          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "In the landscape of AI-powered audio synthesis, Kokoro text to speech offers a high-fidelity solution for converting text into natural speech. This guide delivers actionable advice for API teams aiming to deploy Kokoro efficiently in production systems."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "h2",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Core Concepts of Kokoro Text to Speech"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Kokoro text to speech utilizes a neural network architecture designed for real-time inference, supporting diverse languages and voice profiles. Key elements include the text normalization module, acoustic model, and vocoder. For API integration, focus on the RESTful endpoints that handle synthesis requests and return audio streams in formats like WAV or MP3."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "h2",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Setting Up Kokoro Text to Speech Integration"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Begin by configuring your API client to interact with Kokoro endpoints. Here's a concise example using cURL:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "code_block",
        "lang": "bash",
        "value": "curl -X POST https://api.kokoro.ai/v1/synthesize \\\n  -H \"Authorization: Bearer YOUR_API_KEY\" \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\"text\": \"Welcome to our service.\", \"voice\": \"en-US-Neural\", \"speed\": 1.2}'",
